WEBVTT

00:02.461 --> 00:04.461
♪

00:05.798 --> 00:08.248
Art lovers of springfield,
good news.

00:08.250 --> 00:10.926
The art museum
is closed forever!

00:10.928 --> 00:12.469
[scattered applause]

00:12.471 --> 00:15.597
Instead, our entire collection
will be digitized

00:15.599 --> 00:18.183
And sold for a fortune
on the blockchain

00:18.185 --> 00:22.146
As non-fungible tokens, or nfts.

00:22.148 --> 00:24.857
Whatever the hell those are.

00:24.859 --> 00:25.983
[chuckles]

00:25.985 --> 00:28.527
Now let's turn
some of our crappy art

00:28.529 --> 00:29.987
Into computer money.

00:29.989 --> 00:33.657
Starting with
a true masterpiece, my butt.

00:33.659 --> 00:36.118
[laughs]

00:38.330 --> 00:39.747
[whirring]

00:39.749 --> 00:40.831
Uh, dad?

00:40.833 --> 00:42.791
Ah! Technology!

00:42.793 --> 00:44.168
[phone chimes]

00:45.588 --> 00:47.713
I've lost bart forever!

00:47.715 --> 00:49.715
No!

00:51.469 --> 00:52.634
[cash register rings]

00:52.636 --> 00:54.678
Yes!

00:57.558 --> 00:59.058
[whirring]

00:59.060 --> 01:02.186
Honey? Remember how
we're always saying

01:02.188 --> 01:04.104
We wish bart was less fungible?

01:04.106 --> 01:05.939
Did something happen to bart?

01:05.941 --> 01:07.232
Only the parts you can hug.

01:07.234 --> 01:10.152
The rest is alive,
right here on my phone.

01:10.905 --> 01:13.739
[yelps] my baby is an app!

01:13.741 --> 01:15.657
Uh, no, apps actually do stuff.

01:15.659 --> 01:16.992
He's an nft.

01:16.994 --> 01:19.078
-But look how much he's worth.
-[gasps]

01:19.080 --> 01:20.996
For bart? Hmm.

01:20.998 --> 01:23.916
Imagine what we'd get for lisa.

01:23.918 --> 01:27.211
He is the first nft
of an actual person.

01:27.213 --> 01:28.295
I don't care.

01:28.297 --> 01:30.506
We've got to find a way
to get him back.

01:30.508 --> 01:34.802
[hooded figure]
to do that, you, yourself
must enter the blockchain.

01:34.804 --> 01:36.011
Who are you?

01:36.013 --> 01:38.222
We are the enlightened
intellects

01:38.224 --> 01:40.390
Who safeguard the crypto-verse.

01:41.435 --> 01:43.685
[homer]
kylie jenner, rob gronkowski,

01:43.687 --> 01:44.978
And jimmy fallon.

01:44.980 --> 01:47.189
I thought you were
just celebrity shills.

01:47.191 --> 01:50.192
Ugh, we would never
promote a technology

01:50.194 --> 01:52.361
If we didn't understand
the distributed ledger

01:52.363 --> 01:53.445
Underpinning it.

01:53.447 --> 01:54.530
Der!

01:54.532 --> 01:57.533
[laughs] I can't
stop laughing, buddy.

01:57.535 --> 01:58.659
[homer]
shut up.

01:58.661 --> 02:00.327
You ruined "cowbell."

02:03.707 --> 02:05.541
This key is a back door

02:05.543 --> 02:08.460
Through the blockchain's
cryptographic protocol.

02:10.381 --> 02:12.881
Once you're inside, find bart

02:12.883 --> 02:14.925
And use it to get
both of you out.

02:14.927 --> 02:16.385
[grunts]

02:16.387 --> 02:18.595
[whirring]

02:22.017 --> 02:24.393
Huh, so this is the blockchain.

02:24.395 --> 02:27.512
No, noob, this is
the block-train.

02:28.732 --> 02:31.150
<i> Speeding forever through</i>
<i> the loveless icy world</i>

02:31.152 --> 02:32.901
<i> Created by crypto-bros.</i>

02:32.903 --> 02:36.238
<i> Powered by the most abundant</i>
<i> fuel in the universe:</i>

02:36.240 --> 02:39.575
<i> Fomo, the fear of missing out.</i>

02:39.577 --> 02:43.579
For a digital incarnation of an
abstract mathematical concept,

02:43.581 --> 02:45.497
It could use a good dusting.

02:45.499 --> 02:48.667
[british accent]
well, that's because this is the
last car of the train, innit?

02:48.669 --> 02:52.337
The dwelling place of nfts
with no value.

02:52.339 --> 02:56.592
Which is 99% of all nfts
ever created.

02:56.594 --> 02:59.845
Huh, I guess being
the second-ever human nft

02:59.847 --> 03:01.263
Isn't worth a whole lot.

03:01.265 --> 03:03.140
Where do they keep my son?

03:03.142 --> 03:05.559
[french accent]
at the very front of the train

03:05.561 --> 03:07.060
Where you can never go.

03:07.062 --> 03:08.353
Watch me!

03:08.981 --> 03:10.397
[grunts]

03:10.399 --> 03:13.192
[laughter]

03:13.194 --> 03:14.484
Whoa!

03:17.573 --> 03:21.325
[retching]
you killed ennui oeuf 116.

03:23.621 --> 03:24.661
[whirring]

03:26.165 --> 03:29.082
Congratulations,
you've moved up the train

03:29.084 --> 03:31.460
Because you are now
as valuable as us,

03:31.462 --> 03:32.711
The cuddle kittens.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.796
Because you killed another nft.

03:34.798 --> 03:36.757
What you call
mindless slaughter,

03:36.759 --> 03:38.759
Crypto-bros call "disruption,"

03:38.761 --> 03:40.427
And then pour cash into it.

03:40.429 --> 03:42.137
So, to rescue bart,

03:42.139 --> 03:44.306
I need to kill
a bunch of you guys.

03:46.894 --> 03:48.393
[popping]

03:50.439 --> 03:51.730
Ooh.

03:51.732 --> 03:53.774
Well, I guess I got to do this.

03:53.776 --> 03:55.359
[yowling]

03:56.028 --> 03:59.196
Sorry! Nothing personal!

04:01.617 --> 04:06.078
Hope... You... Can't...
Feel... Pain. [grunts]

04:07.498 --> 04:08.747
[whirring]

04:29.436 --> 04:30.477
[whirring]

04:32.314 --> 04:34.064
[lisa]
mom's price is skyrocketing!

04:34.066 --> 04:35.774
Look at the fomo!

04:35.776 --> 04:39.194
Now everyone's gonna
want human nfts.

04:39.196 --> 04:42.197
Dad, you said you were
taking me to bumper boats.

04:42.199 --> 04:45.242
I am. Uh, have
some more chocolate milk.

04:47.204 --> 04:50.622
No one is putting another child
into that scanner...

04:50.624 --> 04:52.541
Before mine.

04:53.544 --> 04:55.460
-[grunting]
-hey!

04:55.462 --> 04:56.670
[whirring]

04:58.299 --> 04:59.131
[gasps]

04:59.133 --> 05:01.675
Please kill ralph-house.

05:02.678 --> 05:04.011
[squishing]

05:04.763 --> 05:07.014
[whirring]

05:08.851 --> 05:12.394
The front of the train.
I made it.

05:13.230 --> 05:15.939
Bart! We're getting out of here!

05:15.941 --> 05:18.066
Whoa, mom, what's the rush?

05:18.068 --> 05:20.736
Grab yourself a jaded ape
and take a load off.

05:20.738 --> 05:23.530
You never like my friends.

05:23.532 --> 05:25.615
Mom's almost got bart out.

05:25.617 --> 05:28.535
Don't let your son become
a worthless human again.

05:28.537 --> 05:30.078
Sell him to me

05:30.080 --> 05:32.539
-For $100 million.
-Hmm!

05:32.541 --> 05:35.334
No, dad!
If you sell bart to mr. Burns,

05:35.336 --> 05:38.211
He'll be trapped
on the blockchain forever.

05:38.213 --> 05:40.380
But this is my chance
not to miss out,

05:40.382 --> 05:42.299
After I've missed out
on everything.

05:42.301 --> 05:44.593
The housing bubble,
the first tech bubble,

05:44.595 --> 05:47.262
The second tech bubble,
the current tech bubble.

05:47.264 --> 05:49.514
Just one time,
I want to be the guy

05:49.516 --> 05:52.059
That gives all his money
to bernie madoff!

05:52.061 --> 05:55.187
Mom, get out of there!
Dad's gonna crack!

06:08.035 --> 06:09.326
He did it.

06:09.328 --> 06:10.994
I can't believe he did it.

06:10.996 --> 06:13.413
[whirring]

06:13.415 --> 06:15.582
-We made it.
-Where's homer?

06:15.584 --> 06:17.834
I want to tell him the inside
of his phone smells.

06:17.836 --> 06:19.961
He-he sold himself.

06:19.963 --> 06:21.963
He was so afraid of missing out,

06:21.965 --> 06:24.424
He tokened his own life.

06:24.426 --> 06:26.760
Woo-hoo!

06:26.762 --> 06:29.721
Eternity on
a super swanky train.

06:29.723 --> 06:32.474
Ooh, twerked chicken.

06:34.728 --> 06:37.062
[rumbling]

06:37.064 --> 06:38.897
What happened?

06:38.899 --> 06:41.733
Our fomo, it's gone.

06:43.946 --> 06:46.571
The nft craze is over.

06:46.573 --> 06:49.032
D'oh!

06:53.288 --> 06:56.164
<i> [homer]</i>
<i>ah, the romance of train travel.</i>

07:00.587 --> 07:03.171
♪

07:03.173 --> 07:07.634
♪<i> and it's clearly</i>
<i> to his credit</i> ♪

07:07.636 --> 07:12.597
♪<i> that he is an englishman</i> ♪

07:12.599 --> 07:14.891
♪<i> he remains</i> ♪

07:14.893 --> 07:19.020
♪<i> an eng</i> ♪

07:19.022 --> 07:21.440
♪<i> lish...</i> ♪

07:21.442 --> 07:23.942
Wait. Did you only
ask me to sing

07:23.944 --> 07:26.769
To forestall your gruesome end?

07:26.771 --> 07:30.073
Guilty as charged. [laughs]

07:30.909 --> 07:33.410
-[bart grunting]
-[laughing]

07:33.412 --> 07:35.454
[screams]

07:36.790 --> 07:38.331
Ha!

07:41.962 --> 07:44.129
It was only by
following my hunch

07:44.131 --> 07:46.298
That we found
the east side strangler

07:46.300 --> 07:48.508
On the west side of town.

07:48.510 --> 07:51.303
Can you explain how
you overcame childhood trauma

07:51.305 --> 07:54.264
To become the nation's most
renowned criminal psychologist?

07:54.266 --> 07:57.142
For that story,
you'll have to read my book.

07:57.144 --> 07:59.603
-[school bell rings]
-[indistinct chatter]

08:01.523 --> 08:03.023
Office muntz.

08:03.025 --> 08:04.900
Told you I'd smell you later.

08:04.902 --> 08:06.526
Been a long time.

08:07.488 --> 08:08.737
Ah, look at us.

08:08.739 --> 08:11.406
We thought we were
gonna stay young forever.

08:11.408 --> 08:13.074
Some of us did.

08:13.076 --> 08:16.203
Oh, right, like bart,
because he got murdered.

08:16.205 --> 08:17.871
Speaking of gruesome junk,

08:17.873 --> 08:19.831
We could use your help
on a case.

08:19.833 --> 08:23.627
I'm flattered, but I'm the dean
of the true crime department.

08:23.629 --> 08:25.921
I can't just run off and--

08:25.923 --> 08:27.923
The killer left a message.

08:27.925 --> 08:30.592
And we think it's for you.

08:30.594 --> 08:32.636
♪

08:43.357 --> 08:45.815
Maybe rod flanders
did grow up to become

08:45.817 --> 08:48.568
A shockingly foul-mouthed
prop comedian,

08:48.570 --> 08:50.529
But he didn't deserve this.

08:50.531 --> 08:53.073
Only a super-traumatized
profiler like you

08:53.075 --> 08:55.283
Can piece together
what happened here.

08:55.285 --> 08:56.243
Hmm.

08:56.245 --> 08:57.953
[breathes deeply, sighs]

08:57.955 --> 08:59.621
[lisa]
our killer took his time.

08:59.623 --> 09:01.122
Had fun with it.

09:01.124 --> 09:02.958
Enjoyed a game of solitaire.

09:02.960 --> 09:05.293
Red king on a red queen?

09:05.295 --> 09:07.921
This psycho doesn't
play by the rules.

09:07.923 --> 09:09.464
Damn, she's good.

09:09.466 --> 09:11.383
Here, he had one
of those moments

09:11.385 --> 09:14.970
Where you walk into a room
and forget what you came in for.

09:14.972 --> 09:17.380
How did my guys miss that?

09:17.382 --> 09:18.306
One more thing.

09:18.308 --> 09:20.258
This killer won't stop now.

09:20.260 --> 09:21.977
There will be others.

09:21.979 --> 09:23.687
Sarge, there's been another.

09:27.818 --> 09:30.110
How can he also be the first?

09:30.112 --> 09:31.736
Sarge, we got another one.

09:32.864 --> 09:34.239
[whistles]

09:34.241 --> 09:35.782
Boy, that's something
you don't see every--

09:35.784 --> 09:37.367
One more, sarge.

09:38.287 --> 09:40.120
Got another one, sarge.

09:40.122 --> 09:41.830
The severed hand
opens the fridge,

09:41.832 --> 09:43.707
Which tugs on that
strip of sinew,

09:43.709 --> 09:44.958
Turning over the eyeball cup,

09:44.960 --> 09:47.294
Which rolls down the spine,
startles a cat,

09:47.296 --> 09:49.462
Which leaps onto
the butter dish seesaw,

09:49.464 --> 09:51.673
And sends
the other eyeball flying,

09:51.675 --> 09:53.508
Turning on the coffee maker.

09:53.510 --> 09:56.845
Even I can't get inside
a mind this deranged.

09:56.847 --> 09:59.973
There's only one person who can.

10:01.602 --> 10:02.809
[thunder rumbles]

10:02.811 --> 10:04.352
Little lisa simpson.

10:04.354 --> 10:06.021
You really made something
of yourself

10:06.023 --> 10:08.148
After I made mincemeat
of your brother.

10:08.150 --> 10:09.566
Come to thank me?

10:09.568 --> 10:11.526
-No.
-Rude.

10:11.528 --> 10:13.528
I don't have time
for your games, bob.

10:13.530 --> 10:14.571
I'm working on a--

10:14.573 --> 10:15.655
Yes, a case so confounding

10:15.657 --> 10:17.532
You're actually willing
to seek my help.

10:17.534 --> 10:20.827
The rube goldberg sherri
is actually quite impressive.

10:20.829 --> 10:22.120
Hat tip, psychopath.

10:22.122 --> 10:24.205
What about
the identical messages?

10:24.207 --> 10:26.991
How can they all be "the first"?

10:26.993 --> 10:28.460
Really, professor simpson,

10:28.462 --> 10:31.129
Am I meant to spoon-feed you
all the answers?

10:31.131 --> 10:33.965
Speak in riddles or drop a clue
in a clever anagram

10:33.967 --> 10:36.801
Hidden in something
I've just said right now.

10:36.803 --> 10:38.261
This is a waste of time.

10:38.263 --> 10:40.055
Perhaps a limerick will help.

10:40.057 --> 10:41.973
There once was a shiny machete,

10:41.975 --> 10:44.225
That turned poor bart's head
to spaghetti.

10:44.227 --> 10:46.728
You're gonna die
in that cell, bob.

10:46.730 --> 10:48.563
And when that happens,

10:48.565 --> 10:50.023
Wherever I am,

10:50.025 --> 10:52.025
I'll be dancing.

10:58.617 --> 11:02.160
Can you think of anyone who
would've wanted to hurt sherri?

11:02.162 --> 11:05.038
No, everybody loved
my big sister.

11:05.040 --> 11:06.498
Big sister?

11:06.500 --> 11:07.832
You guys were twins.

11:07.834 --> 11:10.418
Yes, but sherri was born first.

11:10.420 --> 11:14.756
Probably makes sense for you
to be my husband now, huh?

11:14.758 --> 11:16.216
Sherri is the first.

11:16.218 --> 11:19.552
Rod flanders, dermott spuckler,
all firstborns,

11:19.554 --> 11:21.054
That's the pattern.

11:21.056 --> 11:22.847
And bob said something
about an anagram

11:22.849 --> 11:24.683
Taking us to the killer's lair.

11:25.686 --> 11:27.560
[gasps] that's it.

11:30.357 --> 11:31.523
[tires screech]

11:36.321 --> 11:37.487
[both gasp]

11:38.657 --> 11:39.656
[clanging]

11:39.658 --> 11:40.699
Stay here.

11:41.702 --> 11:44.160
[creaking]

11:44.996 --> 11:47.372
Hey, meat hooks, hook meat much?

11:47.374 --> 11:49.082
Ha-ha--

11:52.462 --> 11:53.837
Nelson?

11:53.839 --> 11:56.131
Nelson, where are you?

11:58.051 --> 12:00.260
[screams]

12:01.304 --> 12:02.554
[panting]

12:04.391 --> 12:05.682
[gasps]

12:05.684 --> 12:09.060
The killer's lair looks
just like my old bedroom.

12:09.062 --> 12:11.146
But how? Ooh.

12:11.148 --> 12:13.481
Maybe the killer's
on the security footage.

12:15.944 --> 12:18.820
No! It can't be!

12:18.822 --> 12:21.114
[grunts] freeze!

12:21.116 --> 12:22.240
-[handcuffs click]
-wha...?

12:22.242 --> 12:23.825
I can't be the killer!

12:23.827 --> 12:26.369
I turned my trauma into healing!

12:26.371 --> 12:27.996
Oprah said so!

12:27.998 --> 12:29.664
[thunder rumbling]

12:29.666 --> 12:32.041
I'm sorry for the imbroglio,
but if the chef de cuisine

12:32.043 --> 12:34.711
Insists on calling it
taco tuesdays,

12:34.713 --> 12:36.713
He can't very well serve flautas

12:36.715 --> 12:38.715
And expect us not
to make a fuss.

12:38.717 --> 12:40.216
[door locks]

12:41.511 --> 12:43.094
Hello, bob.

12:43.096 --> 12:45.472
H-how did you get in here?

12:45.474 --> 12:47.807
Well, I knew if I killed
enough people

12:47.809 --> 12:50.059
In the most gruesome
possible ways,

12:50.061 --> 12:52.228
They'd send me to your prison.

12:52.230 --> 12:54.189
But to get into your cell?

12:54.191 --> 12:56.232
I had a little help.

12:59.863 --> 13:01.404
Lisa the killer.

13:01.406 --> 13:03.281
I never thought
you had it in you.

13:03.283 --> 13:06.242
The lisa you knew didn't.

13:06.244 --> 13:08.536
But I'm another story.

13:08.538 --> 13:10.038
Oh, really?

13:10.040 --> 13:11.915
Split personalities?

13:11.917 --> 13:13.249
Trope alert!

13:13.251 --> 13:15.710
Call the first thought police.

13:15.712 --> 13:17.796
Professor lisa had no idea

13:17.798 --> 13:19.631
<i> She was my accomplice.</i>

13:23.011 --> 13:24.803
But she's gone now.

13:24.805 --> 13:26.596
She was my last victim.

13:26.598 --> 13:29.599
Or, rather, second to last.

13:29.601 --> 13:31.726
The penultimate.

13:31.728 --> 13:33.436
[grumbles]

13:36.483 --> 13:38.983
♪<i> he remains an</i> ♪

13:38.985 --> 13:42.111
♪<i> en-en-en-en-en-en-en-en</i> ♪

13:42.113 --> 13:44.072
♪<i> en...</i> ♪

13:44.074 --> 13:47.659
-[screaming]
-♪<i> ...Glishman.</i> ♪

13:52.707 --> 13:54.457
[munching]

13:54.459 --> 13:55.792
Simpson.

13:55.794 --> 13:57.710
No eating in the turbine room.

13:57.712 --> 13:59.087
Since when?

14:01.258 --> 14:04.008
Pfft. The nanny state
wins again.

14:04.010 --> 14:06.094
No tanning in the reactor core,

14:06.096 --> 14:08.346
No texting while driving
and eating ribs.

14:08.348 --> 14:10.890
Can't even trim your hedges
with a machine gun.

14:10.892 --> 14:12.559
When did everyone get so scared?

14:12.561 --> 14:16.437
The world would be fine if
people just used common sense.

14:16.439 --> 14:17.605
Like me.

14:17.607 --> 14:19.065
Ah! Jailbreak!

14:31.997 --> 14:34.706
Woman. Woman.

14:38.712 --> 14:41.963
Homer, one. Nanny state, zero.

14:41.965 --> 14:43.464
[munching]

14:44.467 --> 14:47.051
[groaning]

14:47.053 --> 14:48.761
[gurgling]

14:48.763 --> 14:51.264
Stupid radioactive garbage donut

14:51.266 --> 14:54.225
Mutating my dna while I sleep.

14:56.396 --> 15:00.273
Hey, who stole
my flanders's newspaper?

15:00.275 --> 15:01.524
Sorry about that, homer-ino,

15:01.526 --> 15:04.611
But I-I whited out the crossword
after I did it,

15:04.613 --> 15:06.029
So you could enjoy it, too.

15:06.031 --> 15:07.906
[gurgling]

15:07.908 --> 15:10.158
-[belches]
-ah.

15:10.160 --> 15:12.869
Better from the chimney
than the furnace, am I right?

15:12.871 --> 15:14.454
[laughs]

15:14.456 --> 15:15.788
[groans]

15:15.790 --> 15:19.125
So, you see, there's nothing
in the bible that says

15:19.127 --> 15:23.463
A pastor and his wife
can't take separate vacations.

15:23.465 --> 15:25.048
[grunts softly]

15:27.427 --> 15:31.012
Daddy, are you being tickled
by the holy spirit?

15:31.014 --> 15:32.972
[gurgling]

15:32.974 --> 15:35.391
[moaning]

15:39.648 --> 15:43.524
[gasps] I've been neighborino'd
into home-diddly-omer.

15:43.526 --> 15:47.528
[gasps] and why am I in church
when football is on?

15:47.530 --> 15:48.696
[all gasping]

15:48.698 --> 15:49.948
[belches]

